Looking at the implementation of `TreeMap` on [grepcode.com][1], 
it has these constructors (among others):

    public TreeMap(Map&lt;? extends K, ? extends V&gt; m) {
        comparator = null;
        putAll(m);
    }

    public TreeMap(SortedMap&lt;K, ? extends V&gt; m) {
        comparator = m.comparator();
        try {
            buildFromSorted(m.size(), m.entrySet().iterator(), null, null);
        } catch (java.io.IOException cannotHappen) {
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException cannotHappen) {
        }
    }

So it makes a difference when you create a new `TreeMap` from a `Map` or a `SortedMap` (such as another `TreeMap`). In case of the latter, it will not re-sort.


  [1]: http://grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/openjdk/8u40-b25/java/util/TreeMap.java#TreeMap.%3Cinit%3E%28java.util.SortedMap%29

